  "prompt": "Is there a maximum limit for a transaction via Net Banking through an SBI account?",
  "response": "Yes, State Bank of India (SBI) does have transaction limits for net banking, which can vary based on the type of transaction and the account type. Typically, for NEFT and IMPS transactions, there are limits set for daily transfers. For example, IMPS transactions often have a limit of up to \u20b92 lakh per transaction, while NEFT transactions may have limits depending on the category of the account and the specific banking regulations.\n\nFor specific and the most updated information, it\u2019s best to check SBI's official website or contact their customer service, as these limits can change based on bank policies or regulatory requirements.",
